  <LabShell
    num="LAB 01"
    title="Why <code>counter++</code> loses updates"
    tag="PDF Q13 · Q40"
    why='<b>Where this bites you:</b> they show you <code>volatile uint32_t counter; counter++;</code> and ask "is this safe?" Step through the exact interleaving below until you can narrate it from memory.'
    takeaway='<b>Say this in the interview:</b> "<code>volatile</code> forces the read and write to happen, but <code>++</code> is still LOAD → ADD → STORE. A preemption between LOAD and STORE loses an update. Fix: critical section (<code>taskENTER_CRITICAL</code>), interrupt masking, an atomic (LDREX/STREX), or a single-writer design."'
